                </div>
                <p>The Indian motorcycle market has matured significantly, with a growing demand for premium, performance-oriented motorcycles. Yamaha's decision to bring the MT-07 to India is a strategic move to tap into this segment. While official details are still scarce, we can glean a lot from the latest international models and what has been showcased in India previously.</p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Expected Specifications & Features</h3>
                <p>The new Yamaha MT-07 is expected to be a powerhouse of features and performance, mirroring its international counterparts. Here’s a breakdown of the key specifications and features you can likely look forward to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Engine:</span> The heart of the machine will be the 689cc, liquid-cooled, DOHC, parallel-twin, CP2 engine. It is expected to be Euro 5+ compliant, which aligns with India's BS6 emission norms. This engine is renowned for its strong low-end torque and impressive power output.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Power & Torque:</span> Expect the engine to produce around 73.4 PS of power at 8,750 rpm and 67 Nm of torque at 6,500 rpm. This power delivery is designed for a thrilling yet manageable riding experience.</li>
                    <li> <span class="font-weight-700">Transmission: </span>A 6-speed constant mesh gearbox will handle the power, and it will likely be equipped with an assist and slipper clutch for smoother downshifts and reduced lever effort.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Chassis & Suspension: </span>The bike will feature a high-strength steel diamond frame. The suspension setup is expected to be a 41mm inverted telescopic fork at the front and a link-type rear monoshock, adjustable for preload and rebound damping.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> Brakes: </span>For excellent stopping power, the MT-07 will likely feature twin 298mm rotors with radially mounted calipers at the front and a single 245mm disc at the rear. A dual-channel ABS system will be standard for enhanced safety.</li>
                    <li> <span class="font-weight-700"> Electronics & Technology: </span>This is where the new MT-07 shines. It is anticipated to come with a new 5-inch full-color TFT instrument cluster. This display will offer smartphone connectivity via the MyRide app, allowing riders to get call and message notifications. It may also feature a Y-AMT (Yamaha Automatic Manual Transmission) as an option, which would be a game-changer. Other features include a Yamaha Chip Controlled Throttle (YCC-T) with riding modes, switchable traction control, and self-cancelling turn signals.</li>
                    <li> <span class="font-weight-700">  Design:</span> The 'Hyper Naked' design language is evident in its aggressive and minimalist styling. The new model is expected to feature a distinct minimalist LED headlight, a sculpted fuel tank, and a compact body, all contributing to its raw, muscular look.</li>
                </ul>
