                <p>The pricing of the <span class="font-weight-700">MT-07 </span>in India is a critical factor for its success. While Yamaha has not made any official announcements, the industry anticipates a competitive price tag to challenge its rivals. Given the international pricing and considering it will be brought in as a completely built-up unit (CBU), the expected price for the <span class="font-weight-700">Yamaha MT-07</span> in India is likely to be in the range of <span class="font-weight-700">₹7.5 lakh to ₹8.0 lakh (ex-showroom).</span></p>
                <p>As for the launch timeline, the MT-07 has been showcased at various events in India, and there has been a lot of positive buzz. The most plausible launch timeline, according to industry insiders and reports, is somewhere in the <span class="font-weight-700">Nov 2025.</span> It’s a wait that is sure to test the patience of many, but if the anticipation is anything to go by, it will be well worth it.</p>
